{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":17206,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-17T17:13:02.819Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIs it possible to use the Skybox material as the environment map for reflective materials? Ideally this would also work with the PBR pipeline. My understanding is that currently only a TextureCube resource can be used - and in the case of PBR, only the texture cube associated with the Zone is used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy goals is just interact with the Skybox material (say, something like this):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/19febbe260deee27c58d67e55888a7c85306d55a.jpg\" width=\"690\" height=\"396\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-17T17:13:02.819Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":109,"reads":62,"readers_count":61,"score":649.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/box-projection-for-reflection-probes/6896","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Box projection for reflection probes","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17208,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-17T17:18:39.716Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFor instance, in the ‚ÄúForwardDepth‚Äù render path, it looks like the viewport is being sampled for a pass called ‚ÄúRefract‚Äù. I don‚Äôt know what that does, but it seems close-ish to what I‚Äôm after‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"depth\" sizedivisor=\"1 1\" format=\"lineardepth\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"1 1 1 1\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" output=\"depth\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"depth\" output=\"depth\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/renderpath\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-17T17:19:01.175Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":17.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17209,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-17T18:37:19.084Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eKind of getting the idea now‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lazyYT\" data-youtube-id=\"pGPO16j-IFM\" data-youtube-title=\"IOGRAM: Screen space reflections\" data-width=\"480\" data-height=\"270\" data-parameters=\"feature=oembed\u0026amp;wmode=opaque\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-17T18:37:19.084Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":63,"readers_count":62,"score":17.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pGPO16j-IFM","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"IOGRAM: Screen space reflections","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"godan","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17232,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-18T14:38:07.071Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo, rather than using some kind of screen space hack, I wrote a reflection probe component. This ties in beautifully with the existing PBR pipeline. Check it out:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lazyYT\" data-youtube-id=\"01OzZ-pSkV0\" data-youtube-title=\"IOGRAM: Reflection Probe\" data-width=\"480\" data-height=\"270\" data-parameters=\"feature=oembed\u0026amp;wmode=opaque\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-20T10:52:46.336Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":102,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":656.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01OzZ-pSkV0","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"IOGRAM: Reflection Probe","clicks":3},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/material-workflow-from-blender/3043/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Material workflow from Blender","clicks":4},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/pbr-problems/1969/27","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"PBR problems","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true},{"id":17236,"name":"","username":"sabotage3d","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/sabotage3d/{size}/87_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-18T15:29:57.935Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNice! Is there any slowdown it is hard to say from the video?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-18T15:29:57.935Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":11.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":151,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17237,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-18T15:35:54.630Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNice! Is there any slowdown it is hard to say from the video?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI haven‚Äôt run the profile on this, but qualitatively, no noticeable performance hit. I‚Äôm using 1024 px^2 for each cube face, which might not be optimal on all platforms/hardware configs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, I haven‚Äôt totally figured out the question of when to update the reflection probe. If nothing is changing, then it is overkill to update every from or even on a fixed update loop. Also, you might just want to have this in the editor and bake the probe to a texture on disk‚Ä¶For now, I‚Äôve just implemented an Update() function that I have tied in to my specific use case.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI was thinking of doing a PR for this - would it be useful to anyone else?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-18T15:37:08.173Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":36.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17239,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-18T19:58:44.353Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eVery\u003c/em\u003e nice\u003cbr\u003e\nFor less-shiny (or smaller) objects you wouldn‚Äôt need as high a resolution since it gets blurred anyway, but this would still make the objects fit really nice into the environment.\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd I guess it would need some interpolation to work well on moving objects?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-18T19:58:44.353Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":16.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3016,"topic_slug":"use-skybox-material-as-reflection-source","display_username":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"username":"godan","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"modera